                <author>
                    <persName xml:lang="en">
                        <forename sort="2">Gregorius</forename>
                        <addName type="family" sort="1">Bar Hebraeus</addName>
                    </persName> — 
                    <persName xml:lang="syr">
                        <forename sort="2">ܓܪܝܓܘܪܝܘܣ</forename>
                        <addName type="family" sort="1">ܒܪ ܥܒܪܝܐ</addName>
                    </persName>
                </author>
                <textLang mainLang="syr"/>
                <!-- check date more precisely-->
                <date to="1285">?-1285</date>
                <note type="abstract" xml:lang="en">The second part of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/239">Bar Hebraeus</persName>' 
                    <bibl>
                        <title>Chronicle</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/2500"/>
                    </bibl>; an account of ecclesiastical history, starting with the 
                    biblical priest <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1534">Aaron</persName> and continuing through <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/239">Bar Hebraeus</persName>' 
                    own time (the 13th century).</note>
                <note type="content-description" source="#bib2502-3" xml:lang="en">Section 1 of the Ecclesiastical History looks primarily west, to the history of the Church
                in the Eastern Roman Empire and of the West Syrian patriarchs, while section 2 deals with the east, the West Syrian maphrians and the Church of the East 
                patriarchs. The greatest value of the chronicle as a historical source is in its perspective on events in the east during Bar Hebraeus' lifetime in 
                the 13th century.</note>
                
                
                <!--<note xml:lang="syr" type="prologue" source="#bib2502-1">
                    <quote>ܐܡܪ ܐܦܢ ܠܐ ܣܦܿܩ ܐܢܐ: ܐܫܬܥܐ ܐܦܢ ܠܐ ܡܘܦܐ ܐܢܐ.</quote>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="fr" type="prologue" source="#bib2502-1" xml:id="prologue2502-1"><quote>Malgré mon insuffisance je dirai, malgré mon incapacité je raconterai.</quote></note>  
                <note type="incipit" source="#bib2502-1" xml:id="incipit2502-1">
                    <seg xml:lang="syr">
                        <quote>ܓܒܝܘܬܗ ܕܝܢ ܕܡܪܝ ܡܝܠܣ ܛܘܒܢܐ ܗܟܢܐ ܗܘܬ. ܕܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܗܘ̣ܐ ܡܢ ܐܬܪܐ ܕܪ̈ܙܝܩܝܐ: ܘܐܬܛܒܥ ܗܘ̣ܐ ܒܛܠܝܘܬܗ ܕܢܫܡܫ ܠܡܠܟܐ ܕܐܪܥܐ.</quote>
                    </seg>
                    <seg xml:lang="fr">
                        <quote>L’élection du bienheureux Mar Mîlès se fit ainsi. Il était originaire du pays de Razîq, et dès son plus jeune âge il avait été désigné pour servir le roi de la terre.</quote>
                    </seg>
                </note>
                <note type="explicit" source="#bib2502-1" xml:id="explicit2502-1">
                    <seg xml:lang="syr">
                        <quote>ܘܗܝܡܢܘ ܥܡܘܪ̈ܝܗܿ: ܕܡܛܠ ܒܘܪܟܬܐ ܕܓܪ̈ܡܐ ܕܙܕܝ̈ܩܐ ܕܣܝܡܝܢ ܒܓܘܗܿ ܠܐ ܐܫܬܠܛܘ ܕܢܥܠܘܢ. ܐܬܟܠܠܘ ܕܝܢ ܩܕܝ̈ܫܐ ܒܬܠܬܥܣܪ ܒܬܫܪܝ ܐܚܪܝ ܒܕܣܗܪܐ.</quote>
                    </seg>
                    <seg xml:lang="fr">
                        <quote>Et ses habitants crurent que, du fait de la bénédiction des os des justes qui y étaient placés, ils n’avaient pas réussi à entrer. Les saints furent couronnés le treize du mois lunaire de Teshrî II.</quote>
                    </seg>
                </note>-->
